<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="120" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,785,1086,1112]" box="[151,785,1086,1112]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,785,1086,1112]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,785,1086,1112]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">
Tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[226,390,1086,1112]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Macrotomini">Macrotomini</taxonomicName>
(Macrotomina) Thomson, 1861
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,1157,1397]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">
The tribe 
<taxonomicName box="[261,407,1157,1182]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="tribe" tribe="Macrotomini">Macrotomini</taxonomicName>
is divided into six subtribes; Macrotomina is composed of 168 species in 46 genera and is the only subtribe with known immature stages. The larva of 
<taxonomicName authority="(Linnaeus, 1767)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1767" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" box="[848,1324,1193,1218]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Archodontes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanopus">
<emphasis box="[848,1119,1193,1218]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Archodontes melanopus</emphasis>
(Linnaeus, 1767)
</taxonomicName>
, from the 
<collectingCountry box="[151,210,1230,1254]" name="United States of America" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">USA</collectingCountry>
, was briefly described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Craighead, F. C." box="[503,703,1229,1254]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" pagination="1 - 24" refId="ref9620" refString="Craighead, F. C. (1915) Larvae of Prioninae. Contributions toward a classification and biology of the North American Cerambycidae. Washington Reporter of United States of Department of Agriculture, 107, 1 - 24." type="journal article" year="1915">Craighead (1915)</bibRefCitation>
. The larva had been compared with 
<taxonomicName authority="Audinet-Serville, 1832" authorityName="Audinet-Serville" authorityYear="1832" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Orthosoma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1109,1235,1229,1254]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">Orthosoma</emphasis>
Audinet-Serville, 1832
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Packard, A. S." box="[255,433,1265,1290]" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" pagination="1 - 957" refId="ref10304" refString="Packard, A. S. (1890) Insects injurious to forest and shade trees. 5 th Report of the United States Entomological Commission, Washington 7, 1 - 957." type="journal article" year="1890">Packard (1890)</bibRefCitation>
. Based on the brief description, the larva of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1767" box="[959,1114,1265,1290]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Archodontes" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="120" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melanopus">
<emphasis box="[959,1114,1265,1290]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="120">A. melanopus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterized by having: integument smooth, shining with sparse setae; abdominal segments with retractile ambulatory ampullae not divided by a median impressed line; epistomal margin projected above clypeal base in two broadly triangular lobes; legs present.
</paragraph>
